D_TEXT You have been entrusted with the selection of personnel.
D_TEXT Their lives are in your hands.
D_TEXT I expect you will make the right choices.
D_TEXT A classic thought experiment in the field of ethics
D_TEXT involving the route of a trolly along it's track.
D_TEXT Originally raised by the British philosopher Philippa Foot,
D_TEXT the issue has been considered by philosophers around the world.
D_TEXT There are five workers in the path of a runaway trolley.
D_TEXT You could flip a lever to divert the trolley,
D_TEXT but in doing so doom a single worker on the other track to being ran over instead..
D_TEXT If you could sacrifice one life to save 5, would you do it?
D_TEXT In essense, the Trolley Problem asks the question if it's okay to intentionally kill a person
D_TEXT even if it means saving others.
D_TEXT To start, please choose who to \C[18]sacrifice.\C[0]
